name: NER-RE Pipeline
one_line_profile: Spacy-based pipeline for Named Entity Recognition, Linking, and Relation Extraction
detailed_description: A comprehensive NLP pipeline built on Spacy v3 that performs Named Entity Recognition (NER), Entity Linking to a Knowledge Base, and Relation Extraction. It is designed to extract entities, normalize them, and identify relationships within text.

name: OntoMerger
one_line_profile: Ontology alignment library for deduplicating knowledge graph nodes
detailed_description: A Python library developed by AstraZeneca for ontology alignment and knowledge graph deduplication. It helps in merging overlapping concepts from different ontologies into a unified hierarchy, essential for maintaining clean biological knowledge graphs.

name: argNorm
one_line_profile: Antibiotic Resistance Gene (ARG) normalization tool
detailed_description: A tool to normalize Antibiotic Resistance Genes (ARGs) by mapping them to the Antibiotic Resistance Ontology (ARO). It supports outputs from various ARG prediction tools like DeepARG, ARGs-OAP, and Abricate.

name: MedCAT
one_line_profile: Medical Concept Annotation Tool for biomedical text
detailed_description: A highly efficient Natural Language Processing tool for extracting, linking, and normalizing medical concepts from Electronic Health Records (EHRs) and biomedical text. It uses unsupervised learning to build concept databases and performs Named Entity Recognition and Linking (NER+L).

name: MedCATtrainer
one_line_profile: Interactive interface for training and improving MedCAT models
detailed_description: A web-based interface designed to inspect, improve, and add concepts to MedCAT models. It allows for active learning and manual annotation to create high-quality training datasets for biomedical Named Entity Recognition and Linking.

name: CogStack NLP
one_line_profile: NLP pipeline and platform for clinical data analysis
detailed_description: The core NLP component of the CogStack platform, designed to process and analyze unstructured clinical data. It integrates tools like MedCAT to enable information extraction and enterprise-level clinical search and analytics.

name: OXO
one_line_profile: Ontology cross-reference and mapping service
detailed_description: A service provided by EMBL-EBI for finding mappings (cross-references) between terms from different ontologies, vocabularies, and coding standards. It allows users to traverse the network of ontology mappings.

name: OntoString

name: ZOOMA

name: Bio-YODIE

name: HugeGraph
one_line_profile: Scalable distributed graph database

It supports the Apache TinkerPop Gremlin query language and is suitable for managing large-scale scientific knowledge graphs and biological networks.

name: Apache Jena
one_line_profile: Framework for Semantic Web and Linked Data applications
detailed_description: Apache Jena is an open-source Java framework for building Semantic Web and Linked Data applications. It provides a comprehensive API for RDF data processing, a SPARQL query engine (ARQ), and an inference engine for reasoning over ontologies (OWL/RDFS), making it a foundational tool for bioinformatics knowledge graphs.

name: Apache TinkerPop
one_line_profile: Graph computing framework
detailed_description: Apache TinkerPop is a graph computing framework that provides a standard interface (Gremlin) for graph databases (OLTP) and graph analytic systems (OLAP). It enables researchers to write complex graph traversals and algorithms that are portable across different graph systems.

name: ArangoDB
one_line_profile: Native multi-model database for graph, document, and key-value data
detailed_description: ArangoDB is a native multi-model database that supports graph, document, and key-value data models within a single engine. It provides a powerful query language (AQL) and built-in graph algorithms, making it highly effective for storing and analyzing heterogeneous scientific data and knowledge graphs.

name: ArangoPipe

name: FastGraphML

one_line_profile: TensorFlow implementation of TransE and extended Knowledge Graph Embedding models
detailed_description: A TensorFlow-based implementation of TransE and its variants for knowledge representation learning, enabling integration with TensorFlow ecosystems.

name: DeepPBS
one_line_profile: Geometric deep learning model for predicting protein–DNA binding specificity
detailed_description: A geometric deep learning framework that predicts protein-DNA binding specificity by modeling the geometry and physicochemical properties of the molecular interface.

name: TorchKGE
one_line_profile: PyTorch-based library for Knowledge Graph Embedding
detailed_description: A Python library for knowledge graph embedding (KGE) built on PyTorch, providing efficient implementations of various KGE models and utilities for training and evaluation.

name: TypeDB Bio
one_line_profile: Biomedical Knowledge Graph schema and data loader for TypeDB
detailed_description: A specialized schema and data integration tool for creating a biomedical knowledge graph within TypeDB, facilitating the querying and reasoning over complex biological data.

name: LibKGE
one_line_profile: Reproducible Knowledge Graph Embedding library
detailed_description: A PyTorch-based library for knowledge graph embedding (KGE) focused on reproducibility, hyperparameter optimization, and providing a standardized environment for KGE research.

name: torchlensmaker
one_line_profile: Differentiable geometric optics and optical system design in PyTorch
detailed_description: A tool for differentiable geometric optics simulation and optimization, allowing the design of optical systems using PyTorch's automatic differentiation capabilities.

name: BioKGBench
one_line_profile: Benchmark for AI Agents in Biomedical Science Knowledge Graphs
detailed_description: A benchmarking framework designed to evaluate the performance of AI agents on biomedical knowledge graph tasks, providing datasets and evaluation metrics.

name: GraphSAGE
one_line_profile: Reference implementation of GraphSAGE for inductive representation learning on large graphs
detailed_description: A comprehensive reference implementation of the GraphSAGE algorithm, widely used for generating node embeddings in large-scale biological and chemical networks. It supports inductive learning, allowing for the generation of embeddings for unseen nodes, which is critical for dynamic scientific data.

name: GraphSAGE-Simple
one_line_profile: Simplified reference implementation of GraphSAGE
detailed_description: A simplified and easy-to-understand implementation of GraphSAGE. While less feature-rich than the main repository, it serves as a lightweight tool for quick experimentation and understanding of inductive graph representation learning in scientific contexts.

name: RE-Net (dynamic-KG)
one_line_profile: Recurrent Event Network for reasoning over temporal knowledge graphs
detailed_description: A solver for temporal knowledge graph completion using Recurrent Event Networks (RE-Net). It is designed to model the temporal evolution of facts in knowledge graphs, which is essential for analyzing dynamic biological events and interactions.

name: BioNEV
one_line_profile: Biomedical Network Embedding Evaluation Framework
detailed_description: A comprehensive framework for evaluating graph embedding methods on biomedical networks. It provides a collection of datasets and standard implementations of various graph embedding algorithms to benchmark performance in biomedical tasks like link prediction and node classification.

name: DKRL
one_line_profile: Representation Learning of Knowledge Graphs with Entity Descriptions
detailed_description: An implementation of Description-Embodied Knowledge Representation Learning (DKRL). This tool learns knowledge graph embeddings by incorporating entity descriptions, which is particularly useful for scientific KGs where textual definitions of entities (e.g., proteins, diseases) are rich.

name: DeepPath
one_line_profile: Reinforcement Learning Method for Knowledge Graph Reasoning
detailed_description: A reinforcement learning-based framework for multi-hop reasoning over knowledge graphs. It is widely used to find interpretable paths between entities in large-scale KGs, supporting tasks like drug repurposing and biological pathway discovery.

name: CENET
one_line_profile: Temporal Knowledge Graph Reasoning with Historical Contrastive Learning
detailed_description: A tool for reasoning over temporal knowledge graphs using historical contrastive learning. It captures the evolutionary dynamics of graph structures, applicable to analyzing time-series biological data and event sequences.

name: DeepDrugDomain
one_line_profile: Toolkit for drug-target interaction prediction and binding affinity
detailed_description: A versatile Python toolkit designed for the preprocessing and prediction of drug-target interactions (DTI) and binding affinities. It leverages deep learning models to streamline computational drug discovery workflows.

name: PLNLP
one_line_profile: Pairwise Learning Neural Link Prediction for OGB
detailed_description: A solver specifically designed for link prediction tasks on the Open Graph Benchmark (OGB), which includes large-scale biomedical networks. It utilizes pairwise learning strategies to improve prediction accuracy on scientific graph datasets.

name: NeuralKG
one_line_profile: Open-source Python toolkit for Knowledge Graph Representation Learning
detailed_description: A comprehensive library for knowledge graph representation learning, supporting various KGE models (TransE, RotatE, etc.) and GNN-based models. It is designed to facilitate the development and evaluation of KG embeddings for scientific and general domains.

name: PaperQA
one_line_profile: High-accuracy RAG agent for answering questions from scientific literature with citation grounding
detailed_description: An agentic RAG library designed to retrieve information from scientific papers (PDFs/text) and generate answers with precise inline citations. It minimizes hallucinations by treating search as a multi-step process involving evidence gathering, ranking, and provenance tracking, specifically tailored for scientific workflows.

name: Medical-Graph-RAG
one_line_profile: Graph-based RAG system for evidence-based medical information retrieval
detailed_description: A Retrieval-Augmented Generation system that constructs and utilizes medical knowledge graphs to enhance evidence retrieval and reasoning for medical question answering. It integrates structured knowledge (KG) with unstructured text to improve accuracy and provide evidence chains in medical domains.

name: biogpt.cpp
one_line_profile: High-performance C/C++ inference engine for BioGPT models
detailed_description: A lightweight, efficient port of Microsoft's BioGPT model using ggml, enabling high-speed biomedical text generation and analysis on consumer hardware without heavy dependencies.

name: RAG-HPO
one_line_profile: Automated deep phenotype analysis using LLMs and RAG
detailed_description: A Python-based tool for automated deep phenotype analysis of clinical information. It leverages Large Language Models (LLMs) and Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) to map clinical text to Human Phenotype Ontology (HPO) terms.

name: MedRAG
one_line_profile: Toolkit for Medical Retrieval-Augmented Generation
detailed_description: A comprehensive toolkit and benchmark for Medical Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG). It provides unified interfaces for various retrievers and LLMs to evaluate and improve medical question answering systems.

name: 3DMed-RAG
one_line_profile: Multimodal RAG system for medical consultation
detailed_description: A multimodal medical consultation system (3DMed-RAG) that integrates text, image-text, and 3D medical imaging queries. It features domain-aligned negative rejection mechanisms and enhanced flowchart data processing for high-quality medical diagnosis and consultation.

name: LingYi
one_line_profile: KG-based Multi-modal Medical Conversational QA System
detailed_description: A multi-modal medical conversational question answering system that leverages Knowledge Graphs (KG) to enhance response accuracy and context understanding in medical dialogues.

name: SciTab
one_line_profile: Benchmark and tools for compositional reasoning on scientific tables
detailed_description: A challenging benchmark and associated tools for compositional reasoning and claim verification based on scientific tables. It supports the development of models that can verify facts against tabular scientific data.

name: scientific-claim-generation
one_line_profile: Tool for generating claims for zero-shot scientific fact checking
detailed_description: A tool developed by AllenAI for generating scientific claims to support zero-shot fact checking tasks. It aids in creating synthetic data or test cases for verifying scientific information.

name: SciFact
one_line_profile: Models and data for scientific claim verification
detailed_description: The official repository for the SciFact task, providing models (like VeriSci) and evaluation scripts for verifying scientific claims against a corpus of abstracts. It serves as a standard tool for scientific fact-checking research.

name: Trust-Align
one_line_profile: Framework for measuring and enhancing trustworthiness of LLMs in RAG
detailed_description: A research toolkit providing datasets and methods to measure and improve the trustworthiness of Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) systems through grounded attributions and refusal learning, specifically addressing hallucinations in scientific/factual contexts.

name: RAG2
one_line_profile: Rationale-Guided Retrieval Augmented Generation for Medical QA
detailed_description: A medical question answering framework that employs a rationale-guided retrieval mechanism to enhance the accuracy and explainability of RAG systems in biomedical contexts.

name: MultiVerS
one_line_profile: Model for scientific claim verification against evidence
detailed_description: A deep learning model designed for scientific claim verification, capable of predicting fact-checking labels and identifying rationales from scientific abstracts to support or refute claims.

name: webMedQA
one_line_profile: Large-scale Chinese medical question answering dataset
detailed_description: A comprehensive dataset for Chinese medical question answering, collected from online health consultation platforms, serving as a resource for training and evaluating medical QA and RAG systems.

name: diseaseBERT
one_line_profile: BERT model infused with disease knowledge for health QA
detailed_description: A pre-trained BERT model that incorporates disease knowledge to enhance performance on health question answering, medical inference, and disease name recognition tasks.

name: viBioGPT
one_line_profile: Vietnamese LLM for medical and healthcare QA
detailed_description: A domain-specific Large Language Model fine-tuned for biomedical question answering in the Vietnamese language, addressing the lack of medical AI tools for low-resource languages.

name: medAlpaca
one_line_profile: LLM fine-tuned for medical question answering
detailed_description: A collection of open-source Large Language Models fine-tuned on diverse medical datasets to perform biomedical question answering and information retrieval tasks.

name: paperqa-zotero
one_line_profile: QA tool over Zotero library documents
detailed_description: A workflow tool that integrates Large Language Models with Zotero reference libraries, enabling researchers to perform question answering and evidence retrieval directly from their collected scientific literature.

name: OpenBG
one_line_profile: Large-scale open datasets and benchmarks for domain-specific knowledge graph evaluation
detailed_description: OpenBG provides a suite of datasets designed for evaluating knowledge graph performance in domain-specific scenarios, supporting tasks like knowledge reasoning and completion.

name: ThoughtSource
one_line_profile: Central resource and toolkit for Chain-of-Thought reasoning data and evaluation in science
detailed_description: ThoughtSource is a framework and data hub for Chain-of-Thought (CoT) reasoning, specifically curating scientific and medical QA datasets (like PubMedQA) to evaluate and improve the reasoning capabilities of Large Language Models.

name: metapaths
one_line_profile: R package for similarity search in heterogeneous knowledge graphs using meta-paths
detailed_description: metapaths is an R package that performs similarity search and analysis on heterogeneous knowledge graphs by leveraging meta-path based metrics, useful for omics and network biology analysis.

name: DRKG
one_line_profile: A comprehensive biological knowledge graph and toolkit for drug repurposing
detailed_description: DRKG (Drug Repurposing Knowledge Graph) is a large-scale biological knowledge graph integrating information from six databases including DrugBank, Hetionet, and GNBR. It provides a rich dataset of entities (genes, compounds, diseases) and relations, along with a set of tools and pre-trained embeddings specifically designed to facilitate drug repurposing tasks using graph machine learning.

name: OGB
one_line_profile: Benchmark datasets and evaluators for graph machine learning
detailed_description: Open Graph Benchmark (OGB) is a collection of realistic, large-scale, and diverse benchmark datasets for machine learning on graphs. It includes specific datasets for bioinformatics and chemistry (e.g., molecular property prediction, protein-protein association), providing standard data loaders and evaluation metrics to facilitate reproducible research in AI for Science.
